          Education
          <div class="info">
            My journey into software development started in community college with a painfully slow introduction course into Python. Wanting to challenge myself, I found a Denver local bootcamp called <a href="https://turing.edu/" target="_blank">Turing School of Software & Design</a> and immediately enrolled into their backend program.<br><br>

            Turing is an accredited online school that, over a 7 month long full-time program, focuses on establishing developers with a solid, and practical foundation. This includes everything from self-driven learning, communication, developer empathy, and even challenging our biases - as well as the software development space as a whole.
          </div>
        </div>
